{
  "title": "Immortal, Invisible, God Only Wise",
  "key": "G major",
  "key_root": "G",
  "mode": "major",
  "meter": "3/4",
  "bpm": 100,
  "words": "Walter Chalmers Smith, 1876",
  "music": "or &#39;Joanna&#39; or &#39;Palestrina&#39; traditional Welsh found in, 1839",
  "tune": "St. Denio",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Immortal, invisi- ble, God only wise, In light inaccessible hid from our eyes, Most blessèd, most glorious, the Ancient of Days, Almighty, victorious, Thy great Name we praise.",
    "v2": "Unresting, unhasting, and silent as light, Nor wanting, nor wasting, Thou rulest in might; Thy justice, like mountains, high soaring above Thy clouds, which are fountains of goodness and love.",
    "v3": "To all, life Thou givest, to both great and small; In all life Thou livest, the true life of all; We blossom and flourish as leaves on the tree, And wither and perish but naught changeth Thee.",
    "v4": "Great Father of glory, pure Father of light, Thine angels adore Thee, all veiling their sight; But of Thy rich graces this grace, Lord, impart Take the veil from our face, the vile from our heart.",
    "v5": "All laud we would render; O help us to see &#39;Tis only the splendor of light hideth Thee, And so let Thy glory, almighty, impart, Through Christ in His story, Thy Christ to the heart."
  },
